## File-format conventions (this rule loads on edit)

- **`wrangler.jsonc`** is the modern format ([recommended by Cloudflare](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/wrangler/configuration/) since Wrangler v3.91.0). Use it for all new Workers. JSONC supports comments, which `wrangler.json` does not.
- **`wrangler.toml`** is still supported but some newer features are JSON-only. Keep existing `.toml` files; don't introduce new ones.
- **`.dev.vars`** is the local-dev secrets file (`KEY=value` per line, dotenv format). Must be in `.gitignore`.
- **`worker-configuration.d.ts`** is generated by `wrangler types`. Should be in `.gitignore` OR committed and regenerated in CI; pick one per repo and document it.

