## Reviewer checklist (copy into PR description)

- [ ] Module Workers syntax (`export default {...}` or `class extends WorkerEntrypoint`); no new `addEventListener("fetch", ...)`
- [ ] `Env` type imported from generated `worker-configuration.d.ts`; `satisfies ExportedHandler<Env>` present on the default export
- [ ] No `console.log` of secret bindings; no secrets in error messages or response bodies
- [ ] All fire-and-forget async work wrapped in `ctx.waitUntil()`
- [ ] Cloudflare resources (KV, D1, R2, Queues, DO, Hyperdrive, Service Bindings) declared as bindings in `wrangler.jsonc`; not as env vars
- [ ] Subrequest budget considered; loops use batching where the API supports it
- [ ] No top-level await; no module-scope mutable state; no module-scope `fetch()`
- [ ] `compatibility_date` set; `compatibility_flags` minimal and justified (each flag named in the PR description)
- [ ] Worker-to-Worker calls use Service Bindings + RPC (not public URLs)
- [ ] `wrangler.jsonc` is the source of truth; Dashboard edits forbidden except secret rotation via `wrangler secret put`
- [ ] `wrangler deploy --dry-run` clean; `wrangler types` regenerated; `tsc --noEmit` clean
- [ ] Tests use `@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers` (see `cloudflare-workers-author` skill § "Testing"); not `unstable_dev` (deprecated)

